{"Title":"Walkthrough","Contents":"<p>This page walks you through basic installation and simple uses of ObjectCloud.</p>\n<h1>Download and Install</h1>\n<p>Download ObjectCloud from <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://andrewrondeau.com/ObjectCloud/Releases/\">http://andrewrondeau.com/ObjectCloud/Releases/</a> and extract the zip file to wherever\nyou plan on installing ObjectCloud. ObjectCloud currently does not\ninstall itself and must be started manually. On Mac and Linux,\nObjectCloud requires a recent version of <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html\">Mono</a>. (2.4) See the <a target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"/Docs/requirements.page\">requirements</a> for more information.</p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</span>: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Be careful where you extract ObjectCloud. It might not work if extracted onto a network share, or in a folder synchronized by a utility like <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.getdropbox.com/\">Dropbox</a>.</span><br/>\n</p>\n<h1>Running ObjectCloud</h1>ObjectCloud is a server that is run at the command-line. There is no GUI except for what is seen in the web browser.<br/>\n<h2>Windows</h2>\n<p>Open the directory that you installed ObjectCloud into, and double-click on the ObjectCloud application file. (Either ObjectCloud or ObjectCloud.exe) If you see \"Windows Firewall has blocked some features of this program,\" click \"Allow Access.\"</p><p><img src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/grant%20access.png\"/></p>\n<h2>Mac / Linux</h2>\n<p>Open a shell (terminal) and cd to the directory that ObjectCloud is installed into. Type \"mono ObjectCloud.exe\"</p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</span>: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">ObjectCloud requires </span><a style=\"font-style: italic;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html\">mono</a><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> on Linux and Mac</span>.<br/></p>\n<h1>Viewing ObjectCloud from a browser for the first time</h1>\n<p>ObjectCloud will take about a minute or so to set itself up.&#160;While it is loading, you will see some gibberish fly through the screen.</p><p>When ObjectCloud is ready, you will see a screen like the following:</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"walkthrough/server%20started.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>When ObjectCloud is ready for you to view it in a web browser, it says  \"Server is waiting for a new connection at...\" The URL given is where your web browser can access  ObjectCloud. The URL defaults to the host computer's IP at port 1080. Your URL will most likely be different then the one shown above.<br/></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:</span>&#160;<i>In order for OpenID to work correctly, ObjectCloud needs to know its host name. ObjectCloud also defaults to port 1080</i><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; \">&#160;due to security restrictions in Unixes.</span><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">&#160;Setting a hostname and port are discussed in </span><a style=\"font-style: italic;\" target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"public_internet.page\">Putting ObjectCloud on the public internet</a><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">.</span></p><p>Open a browser using the provided URL: (http://those weird numbers/) Don't forget to use the :1080!</p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:</span> <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">We&#160;recommend&#160;using Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, or Safari. Although we like supporting all browsers, Internet Explorer may have some display glitches and doesn't support all functionality.</span></p><p>If all goes well, you will see a page similar to the following:</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/browser%20opened.png\" align=\"none\"/><br/></p><p>Did you get some error when trying to connect? Make sure you type in the URL displayed from the \"Server is waiting for a new connection at...\" message, including the :1080 part.<br/></p><p>Now that you've connected to ObjectCloud, it's time to log in. For now, log in as root. Type \"root\" into the Username box, and \"root\" into the password box. Click on the \"login\" button. Omit the quotes.<br/></p><p>When you are logged in as root, the page's background becomes red. This is a security feature.</p><h2>Changing Root's password</h2><p><img alt=\"Our gorgeously handsome programmer, Andrew Rondeau, expresses his fear about pickpockets and loose women\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/beware-of-pickpockets-and-l.jpg\" align=\"right\"/>The first thing you should do once you get ObjectCloud running is to change root's password. If you don't do, hackers will fill up your ObjectCloud instance with gremlins, pickpockets, and loose women. They might also blackmail you with pictures from that party in... Oh wait, we agreed never to talk about that again!</p><p>Type in the new root password and click \"change password.\"</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/change%20password.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>You should see a dialog that says, \"Password Changed\"</p><h1>Creating Accounts</h1><p>After setting up a root password, the next step is to create two accounts. Click on \"Change User\" in the upper-right corner of the browser, and then \"Create Account.\"</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://10.0.1.198:1080/Docs/walkthrough/create%20user.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Once on the \"Create Account\" page, type in the user name and password for the new account. In these examples, \"patrick\" and \"ellie\" are the user names.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://10.0.1.198:1080/Docs/walkthrough/create%20account.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>When you click \"create account,\" you will see a dialog stating that the new user was created. Create the second account.</p><blockquote class=\"webkit-indent-blockquote\" style=\"margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;\"><p><b>Note</b>: <i>For security reasons, the default setting is that only root can create users and groups, but you may grant other users permission to create accounts and groups.</i></p></blockquote><h1>Setting Avatars (Profile Pictures)</h1><p>After creating two accounts, (\"patrick\" and \"ellie\" are used in these examples,) click on \"Change User\" and log in as one of the new accounts.</p><p><img src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/log in.png\"/></p><p>Click on \"Files\" on the left of the page.</p><p><img src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/click on files.png\"/></p><p>Under \"Upload,\" click on \"Browse.\"</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://10.0.1.198:1080/Docs/walkthrough/upload%20image.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>The new image should appear as the first entry in the user's list of files. Right-click on the uploaded file name, and select \"Copy Link Location\" (Exact wording may change depending on browser.)</p><p>Click on \"Account\" on the left of the page.</p><p><img src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/click on account.png\"/></p><p>Under \"Change Avatar,\" paste in the link. Remove the domain from the URL so it starts with /Users/... Replace any %20s with a space. (See below)</p><p>Click \"Change Avatar,\" and then refresh. When done correctly, the avatar should change.</p><p><img src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/change avatar.png\"/></p><p>Repeat the above steps for the other user.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>hfdhdf</p><p><br/></p><h1>TODOs</h1><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>Create two accounts</p><p>Change avatars</p><p>Create a status and share</p><p>Reply</p><p>Create a page and share</p><p>Create image, edit, and share</p><h1>Create a Page</h1><p>After changing root's password, click on the \"My Files\" link to access root's files.</p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/my%20files.png\" align=\"none\"/><br/><p>After clicking on \"My Files,\" you will see root's directory. It should be empty.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/empty%20home%20directory.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Click on the \"create\" button to create a new file. You will see a \"new file.page created\" dialog.</p><h2>Edit the Page<br/></h2><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/edit%20file.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Click on the context button next to \"new file.page\". Select \"Edit.\" nicEdit, a simple browser-based page editor, will open in either a new window or tab depending on how your browser is configured. (<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:</span> The <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">nicEdit page is a little wonky on Internet Explorer</span>.)<br/></p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/editor.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Enter a title, type in some text, and then click on the disk icon to save. You will see a dialog with the \"Saved\" message. NicEdit is based on code downloaded from <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://nicedit.com/\" href=\"http://nicedit.com/\">http://nicedit.com/</a>.<br/></p><h2>Include an Image</h2><p>ObjectCloud includes some functionality for including images in .page files.<br/></p><h3>Upload an Image</h3><p>To upload an image go back to the root user's folder. Scroll down to \"Upload\" and click \"Browse.\" Find the image to upload, and click \"Upload.\"</p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</span>: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">When uploading with internet explorer, you will need to rename the file after uploading.</span><br/></p><p><br/></p><h3>Create and Edit an Image (experimental)</h3><p>To create a blank image, create a new file and select one of the image types.<br/></p><p>You can  edit an image by selecting the drop-down menu and choosing \"Edit.\"</p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</span>: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">In-browser image editing is experimental. Internet Explorer is not supported.</span><br/></p><h3>Include an Image<br/></h3><p>To include an image, return to nicEdit. Click on the image icon. Delete the \"http://\" and enter the full path to the image.<br/></p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/include%20image.png\" align=\"none\"/><br/></p><h2>View the created page<br/></h2><p>Go back to the root user's directory.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/view%20new%20page.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Click on \"new file.page\". The document that you just created will open in a new window or tab.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/document%20created.png\" align=\"none\"/><br/></p><h1>Create an Account</h1><p>Open the \"Create Account\" link in a new page or tab. (We will come back to this page when we share files.)<br/></p><p><br/></p><p>Type in the new user's user name and password, then click \"Create Account.\"<br/></p><br/><p>When you click \"create account,\" you will see a dialog stating that the new user was created and you be logged in as the new user.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/account%20created.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:</span> <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">By default, members of the general public can not create accounts on ObjectCloud. Only the root user and members of the administrators group can create accounts. This is to protect an ObjectCloud instance from being overrun by gremlins, hobgoblins, and loose women. By default, anyone can log in with an OpenID.</span><br/></p><h1>Share the page with the new Account</h1><p>Go back to the window or tab with the page you created as the root user. (Don't forget that you're logged in as the account you just created above!) Click refresh. You should see a permission denied error.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/permission%20denied.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Login as root, and then go back to the window or tab with the root user's directory. Click on the context menu button next to \"new file.page.\" (<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:</span> <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Internet Explorer users must right-click in this version.</span>) Select \"Permissions.\"</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/open%20permissions.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>The permissions editor should open in a new window or tab.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/add%20permission.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Type in the user name and click \"add\".</p><p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:</span> <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">You can grant permissions to an OpenID. This allows anyone to view a file without having an account on this instance of ObjectCloud.</span><br/></p><p>When you click \"add,\" you will see a dialog with \"Permission Set to Read\" and the newly added permission will show in the GUI.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/permission%20added.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p>Go back to the tab or window that's viewing \"new file.page.\" Click the \"logout\" button, then log in as the new user. You should see the file.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/shared%20with%20gwbasic.png\" align=\"none\"/><br/></p><p>You can also share the file with people who aren't logged in by sharing with \"everybody.\" You will need to re-log in as root before you can modify the permissions on \"new file.page.\"<br/></p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/add%20permission%20for%20everybody.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/shared%20with%20everybody.png\" align=\"none\"/></p><h1>Stopping ObjectCloud</h1>\n<p>On Windows, ObjectCloud stops when a key is pushed. On Linux or\nMac, ObjectCloud stops when it gets a SIGINT signal after you push\ncontrol-C.<br/>\n</p>\n<p><a href=\"about.page\">About ObjectCloud</a></p>\n"}